<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 04 at 3:08PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Comanche,
southwestern Caddo and east central Kiowa Counties through 345 PM
CDT...
At 307 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Meers, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Anadarko, Apache, Cyril, Fort Cobb, Boone and Stecker.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
